                            <comment id="14611274" author="vlivanov" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2023 10:43:34 -0700"  >The problem stem from the fact that os::get_sender_for_C_frame assumes that the caller is always has a C frame layout as well. But it&amp;#39;s not always the case. Either os::get_sender_for_C_frame() has to be fixed or SharedRuntime::generate_native_wrapper() adjusted to produce compatible frame layout. </comment>
                            <comment id="14611272" author="vlivanov" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2023 10:39:18 -0700"  >Reproducer:&lt;br/&gt;
diff --git a/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvm.cpp b/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvm.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
index 2ee87ebd096..8611a50c044 100644&lt;br/&gt;
--- a/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvm.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvm.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -1087,6 +1087,13 @@ JVM_END&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;JVM_ENTRY(jclass, JVM_FindLoadedClass(JNIEnv *env, jobject loader, jstring name))&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;ResourceMark rm(THREAD);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
+  if (UseNewCode) {&lt;br/&gt;
+    Thread* t = Thread::current_or_null();&lt;br/&gt;
+    frame fr = os::current_frame();&lt;br/&gt;
+    static char buf[O_BUFLEN];&lt;br/&gt;
+    VMError::print_native_stack(tty, fr, t, false, -1, buf, sizeof(buf));&lt;br/&gt;
+  }&lt;br/&gt;
+&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Handle h_name (THREAD, JNIHandles::resolve_non_null(name));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;char* str = java_lang_String::as_utf8_string(h_name());&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14611271" author="vlivanov" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2023 10:38:26 -0700"  >Candidate fix (doesn&amp;#39;t cover linux-aarch64):&lt;br/&gt;
diff --git a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/os_bsd_aarch64.cpp b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/os_bsd_aarch64.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
index e2696a52475..feda935c6c1 100644&lt;br/&gt;
--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/os_bsd_aarch64.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/os_bsd_aarch64.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -177,7 +177,7 @@ frame os::fetch_compiled_frame_from_context(const void* ucVoid) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;// JVM compiled with -fno-omit-frame-pointer, so RFP is saved on the stack.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;frame os::get_sender_for_C_frame(frame* fr) {&lt;br/&gt;
-  return frame(fr-&amp;gt;link(), fr-&amp;gt;link(), fr-&amp;gt;sender_pc());&lt;br/&gt;
+  return frame(fr-&amp;gt;sender_sp(), fr-&amp;gt;link(), fr-&amp;gt;sender_pc());&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;NOINLINE frame os::current_frame() {&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
